  "response": "Arnab Goswami, a prominent Indian journalist and television news anchor, resigned from Times Now in November 2016. While the specific reasons for his resignation were not publicly detailed, it is widely believed that he wanted to pursue his own venture in the media industry.\n\nAfter leaving Times Now, Goswami co-founded Republic TV, a news channel, which launched in May 2017. His decision to start Republic TV was likely driven by a desire for greater editorial independence and control, allowing him to shape the channel's content and approach according to his vision. Republic TV quickly gained significant viewership and became known for its aggressive style of journalism and debates.\n\nGoswami's move from a high-profile position at Times Now to starting his own media enterprise reflects his entrepreneurial spirit and ambition to create a platform that aligns with his perspectives and methods of news reporting.",
